* GopherJS

- Compiles Go to JavaScript
- Existed since 2015
- Written by Richard Musiol ([[https://github.com/neelance][@neelance]])

.image gopherjs.svg

: GopherJS has allowed Go in the browser since 2015. It's a tool for compiling Go to JavaScript. It was written by Richard Musiol. It supports most of standard library. There are many community bindings for existing web technologies, such as websockets, local storage and others. Very easy to use (see graphic). It remains the most mature way of running Go in the browser, and is used by open source projects such as perkeep.
