* net/http Client

- Built on browser Fetch API
- Supports most request properties (body, headers, context cancellation)
- Supports streaming responses

.image network.svg 350 _
.caption Gopher by [[https://twitter.com/egonelbre][@egonelbre]].

: As mentioned before, the Go standard library http.Client can be used in WebAssembly code. This is possible thanks to a special implementation of the DefaultTransport in the standard library, which uses the browser Fetch API to send requests and receive responses, so anytime you use the DefaultTransport it will all just work. It maps things like the request body, headers and even context cancellation into Fetch parameters. It supports streaming response bodies and delivers the data to the WebAssembly runtime as soon as it has been received.
